"{\"uid\": \"volleyballmag.com-usa-olympics-beach-volleyball-073024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Travis Mewhirter  July 30, 2024    Andy Benesh and Miles Partain won a wild one Tuesday in Paris Olympics beach volleyball, but Chase Budinger and Miles Evans lost, and there was a big upset by the Cubans.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 128, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chase Budinger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\"}, {\"begin\": 153, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.949789635164663, \"rank\": 0.05286472180384683, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}, {\"begin\": 198, \"end\": 204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cubans\", \"score\": 0.9991621659287734, \"rank\": 0.0008385366258339445, \"text\": \"Cubans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cubans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cubans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only USA pair in action Wednesday is Kelly Cheng and Sara Hughes.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 215, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6271370304737931, \"rank\": 0.38976794885042065, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 247, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999991690959901, \"rank\": 8.30904485730765e-07, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 268, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.9999999806104827, \"rank\": 1.6057338244213788e-08, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been upsets during these Olympic Games and there have been commanding victories.\", \"from\": 277, \"to\": 368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there has not been anything quite as bizarre in Paris - even the opening ceremonies did not reach this level of weird - as Andy Benesh and Miles Partain's unexpectedly wild 21-12, 28-26 win Tuesday over Morocco's Mohamed Abicha and Zouheir Elgraoui.\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 421, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0433118862654226e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing about the first 35 minutes of the match suggested anything out of the ordinary.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh and Partain appeared urgent, focused, adjusting from an21-18, 21-18 opening-match lossto Cuba's Jorge Alayo and Noslen Diaz to regain the form that has them as the second seed in Pool D and the ninth overall.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.6491107560868548, \"rank\": 0.5400808967977342, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh and Partain, error-prone and blocked seven times by Alayo on Saturday, did not hit a single error during their 21-12 opening-set victory over Morocco.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the technical timeout of the second set, there were still zero American errors on the board, while Partain had kills on 12 of his 16 attempts.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9952919886350952, \"rank\": 0.004730263694742841, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It all added up to an 18-11 lead that seemed insurmountable.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then, bizarrely, the version of Benesh and Partain that was so convincing during that opening set and established a seven-point second set lead disappeared, replaced by the error-prone edition from Saturday.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Errors, mistakes of both the physical and mental variety compounded into a 9-2 Morocco run, sending the set well into overtime until, at long last, Benesh put it to an end with a block to seal the win, 25-23.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Until he did not.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Abicha, the 44-year-old defender competing in his second Olympic Games, challenged the block.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kevin Wong, doing analysis for NBC, laughed it off.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1830, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Wong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kevin Wong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Wong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Wong\"}, {\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999995033468946, \"rank\": 4.952464074805009e-07, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I call this the challenge from the grave,\\\" he said with a chuckle.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It seemed a challenge out of frustration.\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Abicha was incensed before the point, arguing that Benesh was lathering up the ball in sweat prior to his serve.\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So he challenged for a net fault on Benesh, for seemingly no other reason than because he had one and he can not roll it over into their next match.\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then, unbelievably, the challenge was successful.\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even Wong and Chris Marlowe, doing play-by-play, could not believe it.\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Marlowe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Marlowe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q15117302\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Marlowe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Marlowe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The video showed the net moving, yes, but, as Benesh would emphatically argue after, it was the ball that clipped the net on the way down, not his arm.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh attempted to challenge the challenge which, of course, did not happen.\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On and on he argued - but on the match went, the crowd now fervently on the side of Morocco, the biggest underdogs on the men's side of these Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It could only do so much.\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh and Partain terminated every first-ball in side-out, and At 27-26, a Morocco overset was put away by Benesh to finish off what might not be the most memorable match of these Olympics, but certainly its most bizarre.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2873, \"end\": 2880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most notable result of Tuesday's slate of Olympic beach volleyball matches is Cuba's Jorge Alayo and Noslen Diaz's 21-13, 21-18 sweep over Brazil's George Wanderley and Andre Loyola.\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beach_volleyball\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.037388770625647e-50, \"text\": \"beach volleyball\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beach_volleyball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beach_volleyball\"}, {\"begin\": 3103, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.6491107560868548, \"rank\": 0.5400808967977342, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 3164, \"end\": 3170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999771017153386, \"rank\": 2.1964233840527073e-05, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3180, \"end\": 3189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanderley_(footballer,_born_1988)\", \"score\": 0.6224971980292996, \"rank\": 0.3749999999997412, \"text\": \"Wanderley\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanderley_(footballer,_born_1988)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wanderley_(footballer,_born_1988)\"}, {\"begin\": 3200, \"end\": 3206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loyola_Ramblers_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.99670488770431, \"rank\": 0.0033058560220260097, \"text\": \"Loyola\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loyola_Ramblers_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loyola_Ramblers_men's_basketball\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The win, Cuba's second after sweeping Andy Benesh and Miles Partain, puts Diaz and Alayo in the driver's seat of Pool D, with only Morocco remaining.\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything else has been quite normal, with all of the favorites winning.\", \"from\": 3359, \"to\": 3432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany's Nils Ehlers and Clemens Wickler, in their Olympic debut, swept France wild cards Remi Bassereau and Julien Lyneel, 21-15, 21-17, and it has been sweeps all the way down on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3624, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3434, \"end\": 3441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999918967892866, \"rank\": 7.382609528560503e-06, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3444, \"end\": 3448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nil_Desperandum_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9999983466536858, \"rank\": 9.088476051321674e-07, \"text\": \"Nils\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nil_Desperandum_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nil_Desperandum_GAA\"}, {\"begin\": 3460, \"end\": 3475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clemens_Wickler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clemens Wickler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q15117302\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clemens_Wickler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clemens_Wickler\"}, {\"begin\": 3507, \"end\": 3513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9901410866212601, \"rank\": 0.00995690109054788, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Poland's Bartosz Losiak and Michal Bryl beat Australia's Thomas Hodges and Zach Schubert (21-16, 21-16), Italy's Valentina Gottardi and Marta Menegatti took care of Egypt, and Brazil's Barbara Seixas and Carol Salgado did the same to Lithuania's Monika Paulikiene and Aine Raupelyte.\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3625, \"end\": 3631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999507084869582, \"rank\": 4.929374761473404e-05, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3653, \"end\": 3659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.630475787059266e-23, \"text\": \"Michal\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michal\"}, {\"begin\": 3670, \"end\": 3679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.7604965005773394, \"rank\": 0.30262221193454103, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3682, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Hodges_(Governor_of_Bombay)\", \"score\": 0.5999671382868462, \"rank\": 0.6666666666662905, \"text\": \"Thomas Hodges\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Hodges_(Governor_of_Bombay)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Hodges_(Governor_of_Bombay)\"}, {\"begin\": 3700, \"end\": 3704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zach_Parise\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.5376512283291165e-13, \"text\": \"Zach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zach_Parise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zach_Parise\"}, {\"begin\": 3705, \"end\": 3713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Schubert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7544857850015896e-19, \"text\": \"Schubert\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Schubert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Schubert\"}, {\"begin\": 3730, \"end\": 3735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999853630772855, \"rank\": 1.1377884540216678e-05, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_Menegatti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marta Menegatti\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_Menegatti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_Menegatti\"}, {\"begin\": 3790, \"end\": 3795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999076863, \"rank\": 9.215962614620227e-11, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3801, \"end\": 3807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999771017153386, \"rank\": 2.1964233840527073e-05, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3810, \"end\": 3817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Bush\", \"score\": 0.9996464243825558, \"rank\": 0.00035368169460300256, \"text\": \"Barbara\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Bush\"}, {\"begin\": 3818, \"end\": 3824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Seixas\", \"score\": 0.9999999711026253, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seixas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Seixas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Seixas\"}, {\"begin\": 3859, \"end\": 3868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998501171034, \"rank\": 1.4916213723939053e-07, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chase Budinger and Miles Evans put on a tremendous showing in their Olympic debut, a commanding 21-14, 21-11 victory over France.\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 4039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3910, \"end\": 3924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chase Budinger\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chase_Budinger\"}, {\"begin\": 3935, \"end\": 3940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.949789635164663, \"rank\": 0.05286472180384683, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}, {\"begin\": 4032, \"end\": 4038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9901410866212601, \"rank\": 0.00995690109054788, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such was not the case in their second match.\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stefan Boermans and Yorick de Groot, the top seed in Pool F, dismissed the Americans in convincing fashion in a 21-13, 21-15 win, their second consecutive sweep of these Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 4086, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4086, \"end\": 4092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_Salvatore\", \"score\": 0.9999999863948689, \"rank\": 1.3605081618753557e-08, \"text\": \"Stefan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_Salvatore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_Salvatore\"}, {\"begin\": 4106, \"end\": 4112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorick\", \"score\": 0.9999999995188773, \"rank\": 4.813499382894675e-10, \"text\": \"Yorick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yorick\"}, {\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4399015894846204e-14, \"text\": \"Groot\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Groot\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Errors piled up for the USA, 16 in total by the time the final ball landed.\", \"from\": 4278, \"to\": 4353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4302, \"end\": 4305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6271370304737931, \"rank\": 0.38976794885042065, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the Netherlands played a clean match that bordered on flawless, with just five total errors, three blocks, and three aces.\", \"from\": 4354, \"to\": 4487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4369, \"end\": 4380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9962756047752449, \"rank\": 0.0023495126391185808, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The loss drops Budinger and Evans to 1-1, though they are still a heavy favorite to break pool.\", \"from\": 4489, \"to\": 4584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4517, \"end\": 4522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.949789635164663, \"rank\": 0.05286472180384683, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spain's Adrian Gavira and Pablo Herrera were similarly swept by Boermans and de Groot and took all three sets to beat Gauthier-Rat and Youssef Krou earlier on Tuesday.\", \"from\": 4585, \"to\": 4752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4585, \"end\": 4590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999864444363, \"rank\": 1.355534542233433e-08, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4600, \"end\": 4606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adri\\u00e1n_Gavira\", \"score\": 0.9418719497529063, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gavira\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q15117302\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adri\\u00e1n_Gavira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adri\\u00e1n_Gavira\"}, {\"begin\": 4728, \"end\": 4732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kru_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Krou\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kru_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kru_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France, then, is 0-2, with the final round of pool on August 2.\", \"from\": 4753, \"to\": 4816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4753, \"end\": 4759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9901410866212601, \"rank\": 0.00995690109054788, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Budinger and Evans will break pool with a win over Spain on August 2, or a France loss.\", \"from\": 4818, \"to\": 4905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4831, \"end\": 4836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.949789635164663, \"rank\": 0.05286472180384683, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}, {\"begin\": 4869, \"end\": 4874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999864444363, \"rank\": 1.355534542233433e-08, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4893, \"end\": 4899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9901410866212601, \"rank\": 0.00995690109054788, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Should Budinger and Evans lose to Spain, and France beat the Netherlands, the tiebreak for third will come down to a set-and-point differential.\", \"from\": 4906, \"to\": 5050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4926, \"end\": 4931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.949789635164663, \"rank\": 0.05286472180384683, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}, {\"begin\": 4940, \"end\": 4945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999864444363, \"rank\": 1.355534542233433e-08, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4951, \"end\": 4957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9901410866212601, \"rank\": 0.00995690109054788, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4967, \"end\": 4978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9962756047752449, \"rank\": 0.0023495126391185808, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aside from Cuba's Jorge Alayo and Noslen Diaz upending Brazil's George Wanderley and Andre Loyola, it was an upset-free Tuesday at Eiffel Tower Stadium.\", \"from\": 5052, \"to\": 5204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5063, \"end\": 5067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.6491107560868548, \"rank\": 0.5400808967977342, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 5107, \"end\": 5113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999771017153386, \"rank\": 2.1964233840527073e-05, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_tea